-- South Africa to Appoint Mosimane as National Soccer Coach, Sport24 Reports
-- Nicky Smith
-- 2010-06-25T06:00:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/south-africa-to-appoint-mosimane-as-national-soccer-coach-sport24-reports.html

          
          
             Pitso Mosimane , the assistant coach
to South Africa’s soccer team, known as Bafana Bafana, will
replace Brazilian  Carlos Alberto Parreira  as the head coach of
the national team,  Sport24.com  reported.  
 Mosimane will be announced as Parreira’s replacement soon,
the Cape Town-based website reported, citing senior officials in
the South African Football Association that it didn’t identify.
 Gavin Hunt , considered as a contender for the position, will
continue to manage Supersport United, according to the website.  
